HEADWORD: Epicardium
<hw>Ep`i*car"di*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>'epi`</grk> upon + <grk>kardi`a</grk> heart.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>That part of the pericardium which forms the
outer surface of the heart; the cardiac pericardium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

